		<description><![CDATA[A key to having  a steady flow of traffic to your website is the content.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;">A</span><span> key to having a steady flow of traffic to your website is the quality of the content.  You and your site developer can work to make your site discoverable by including meaningful keywords in your content and having compliant code that can be easily indexed by search engines.  Your website developer/designer can maximize the usability of your site by making sure the navigation is clear.  However, what is most important for getting and keeping site visitors is the content of your website.  In short, visitors will only come to and return to your site if they have a reason. Visitors come and return to sites for content they value.  Generally, people search on the internet for information or to be entertained.</span></p>
<p><span>A successful content strategy should include three critical elements:</span></p>
<ol style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 5px; padding-left: 30px; margin: 0px;">
<li style="margin-top: 5px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style-type: decimal; padding: 0px;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="background-color: transparent;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Creating interesting content</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">.</span></strong></span></span></span><span style="background-color: transparent;"> The buzz on the internet is that you must create &#8220;remarkable&#8221; content.  What is meant by that is content your audience finds useful or entertaining and hopefully good enough that they promote it via social media (Twitter, Facebook, Buzz, Delicious etc.).</span></span></li>
<li style="margin-top: 5px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style-type: decimal; padding: 0px;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="background-color: transparent;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Keeping content fresh</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">.</span></strong></span></span></span><span style="background-color: transparent;"> You can think of fresh content as having &#8220;evergreen&#8221; content.  The idea here is that, you need to add new content on a regular basis.  The interval for adding content needs to be frequent enough that users come back to see what you have added.</span></span></li>
<li style="margin-top: 5px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style-type: decimal; padding: 0px;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="background-color: transparent;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Making it easy to share content</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">.</span></strong></span></span></span><span style="background-color: transparent;"> Visitors to your site need easy access to social media links.  As visitors find interesting and/or helpful content on your website they share the content using social media.  In other words they <em>remark</em> on your content.  The idea that people find your content worth <em>remark</em> is the basis for the &#8220;remarkable&#8221; content terminology.</span></span></li>
</ol>
<p><span>Including a blog as part of your website gives you an easy way to include remarkable content on your site.  Most blogging platforms already include the tools you need to periodically add new content.  Every time you add content a new post is created. Also, tools that allow visitors to your site to share your content using email or social media are either included already or can be added.  These tools are assigned to each post.  By utilizing a blog framework for some or all of your site&#8217;s content you can focus on creating the content rather than the technical ins and outs of presenting it and making it promotable through social media.</span></p>
<p><span>Blogging platforms come in a number of varieties including, hosted versus self hosted, full blog versus mini blogs. In part 2 of this series of posts on blogging I will examine some of the differences in the types of blogging platforms available.</span></p>
<ol style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 5px; padding-left: 30px; margin: 0px;"> </ol>
